# SwiftUI views (HotTub Buddy)

Applies when editing Swift under `Sources/`. Full system: `~/Documents/ui/` + always-on rule `ios-design-system`.

## Screen skeleton

```swift
NavigationStack {
    ScrollView {
        VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 24) {
            // section headings, AppGrouped-style cards
        }
        .padding(.horizontal, 20)
        .padding(.top, 16)
        .padding(.bottom, 24)
    }
    .scrollDismissesKeyboard(.interactively)
    .background(Color(.systemGroupedBackground))
    .navigationTitle("Title")
    .navigationBarTitleDisplayMode(.large)
}
```

## Cards

```swift
.padding(16)
.frame(maxWidth: .infinity, alignment: .leading)
.background(
    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 16, style: .continuous)
        .fill(Color(.secondarySystemGroupedBackground))
)
```

Use `@Environment(\.appPalette) private var palette` and `palette.color(.surfaceCard)` (or matching token) instead of hard-coded fills.

## Primary action

```swift
Button("Save") { }
    .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)
    .controlSize(.large)
    .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)
    .frame(minHeight: 50)
```

## Empty state

Icon (hierarchical SF Symbol) + `.title2.weight(.semibold)` title + `.caption` secondary line; optional single CTA.

## Don’t

- Default `List` for main content screens unless there is a strong reason
- Multiple competing accent colors on one screen
- Bold on every label; font size soup
- Swipe-only actions without an obvious alternative when using ScrollView cards
